message.content:
cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the deployment of small cells and new spectrum sharing schemes for 5G mobile networks.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper may discuss the information theory behind the proposed Centralized Radio Resource Management entity.
- cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) is another possible category as the paper discusses the vision of the SPEED-5G project and explores new paradigms for cellular networks.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the control systems used in the proposed deployment of small cells and spectrum sharing.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but the paper may discuss the impact of the proposed deployment on multimedia applications in 5G networks.
